<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japanese Prime Minister Begins Visit To India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Prime Minister
Yoshiro Mori arrived Monday evening in Bangalore, a southern
Indian city 2,000 kilometers from here, to begin his five-day
visit to the South Asian country, the Press Trust of India (PTI)
reported.
</P>
<P>
In the first visit to India by a Japanese Prime Minister in the
last ten years, Mori flew in Bangalore from Islamabad, Pakistani
capital, after his day-long trip to the neighboring country as
part of his four-nation tour including Bangladesh, Pakistan, India
and Nepal.
</P>
<P>
Tokyo's relation with India, which had come under pressure
following India's nuclear tests in May 1998, is expected to look
up again with the visit of Mori, who is accompanied by a large
delegation.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese Prime Minister is scheduled to arrived here on
Tuesday to hold wide-ranging talks with his counterpart Atal
Behari Vajpayee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
