<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Maldives Supports Indian Proposal on Anti-Terrorism Convention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Maldives supported India's
proposal for a comprehensive international convention against
terrorism scheduled for the United Nations General Assembly
session next month, a spokesman of the Ministry of External
Affairs said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Following a meeting between Indian Prime Minister Atal Behari
Vajpayee and the Maldives President Abdul Gayoom, who arrived here
today for a two-day official visit, the spokesman told the press
that the two sides "articulated their strong common position
against terrorism and fundamentalism".
</P>
<P>
Maldives supported India's initiative on having a comprehensive
international convention against terrorism, he added.
</P>
<P>
At a banquet hosted in honor of the visiting Maldives President
Monday evening, Indian President Kocheril Raman Narayanan appealed
for an early adoption of a convention on terrorism.
</P>
<P>
India has been supplying defense equipment to Maldives which
has a population of 260,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
