<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, August 21 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat arrived in Egypt's
Mediterranean port city of Alexandria Monday on a brief visit for
talks with President Hosni Mubarak on the peace talks between
Israel and the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Arafat will brief Mubarak on his recent visits to European and
Asian countries, during which he explained the Palestinian
positions on the peace process and won their support for the
efforts of the Palestinian people to restore their legitimate
rights, Palestinian Ambassador in Cairo Zohdi Qedra has said. (
Egypt-Palestine-Arafat)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MANILA -- The Philippine government said Monday that it still
expects to resume peace negotiations with the Moro Islamic
Liberation Front (MILF) despite the latter's negative
pronouncements.
</P>
<P>
Edgardo Batenga, chairman of the government peace panel,
downplayed reports in a radio interview that the MILF has
withdrawn the authority given to its peace panel to conduct peace
talks with the government. (Manila-peace proposal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Chief of staff of the Russian Northern Fleet Mikhail
Motsak on Monday officially confirmed the death of the 118 crew
aboard the Kursk nuclear submarine that went down to the bottom of
the Barents Sea on August 12.
</P>
<P>
Mostsak told the state RTR television that all the compartments
of the submarine are filled with water and that none of the
crewmembers survived. (Russia-Submarine-Death) 
</P>
