<HEADLINE> UAE Calls for Defending Jerusalem's Arab Status </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Sultan bin Zayed Al Nahyan,
deputy prime minister of the United Arab Emirates, has called on
the international community to defend the Arab status of Jerusalem
and to totally condemn the Israeli attempts to judaize the city.
</P>
<P>
Sultan, who is also the chairman of the Zayed Centre for
Coordination and Follow-up, made the remark on the 31st anniversary
of the "arson attack" on the Al-Aqsa mosque, reported the official
news agency WAM on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A deranged Australian tourist tried to burned down the Al-Aqsa
mosque 31 years ago. The Al-Aqsa and Dome of the Rock mosques are
located in the Al-Aqsa mosque compound, the third holiest site in
Islam.
</P>
<P>
The day of the "arson attack" on the Al-Aqsa mosque, according
to local media, is to be announced by the Arab and the Islamic
nations as an international day.
</P>
<P>
Sultan said the occasion calls for a unified Arab stance to face
the challenges threatening the Arab nation, adding that Arab
countries in particular, and Islamic and friendly countries must
support the Palestinians in this historic stage of their peaceful
struggle for the establishment of an independent state on their own
land.
</P>
<P>
The fate of Jerusalem is the crux in the final status talks
between Israel and the Palestinians, who have set the September 13
as the target date for a comprehensive peace to end their 50-year
conflict.
</P>
<P>
But the difference over the status of Jerusalem, which claimed
by both Israel and the Palestinians as their capital, has led to
the collapse of the latest Israeli-Palestinian peace talks on July
25.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Sultan also described the Israeli settlements in the
holy city will never change the reality of the city's history,
which is boldly inscribed in the mind and heart of all Arabs and
all peace-loving people in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
