<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sierra Leone Rebels Say Sankoh Is Still Their Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Sierra Leone's rebel Revolutionary
United Front (RUF) said on Tuesday that Foday Sankoh remained to
be its leader and that General Issa Sesay was only interim head of
the group.
</P>
<P>
The British Broadcasting Cooperation (BBC) quoted spokesman for
the RUF Jibril Massaquoi as saying that Issa Sesay would negotiate
with the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) in
Sankoh's absence.
</P>
<P>
Sankoh has been detained by the Sierra Leone government since
his capture in May in the capital Freetown and faces trial for
human rights offences by a court authorized by the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The Sierra Leone government said in a statement on Monday that
RUF' s battlefield commander Issa Sesay was named to replace Foday
Sankoh, adding that it received the information of the leadership
change from Nigerian President Olusegun Obasanjo and Malian
President and ECOWAS chairman Alpha Konare who are on a mission to
Sierra Leone and Liberia to try to restore peace process in Sierra
Leone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
