<HEADLINE> Egyptian FM, Russian Mideast Envoy Discuss Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr
Moussa met on Tuesday with Russian Middle East envoy Vassily Sredin
to discuss the latest developments of the Mideast peace process.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, which took place in Egypt's Mediterranean port city
of Alexandria, dealt with the intensive contacts and consultations
by the concerned parties on the Palestinian-Israeli peace talks,
Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Sredin, deputy foreign minister for Middle East affairs, said
during the meeting that Russia has the desire to play an active
role in the peace process, which it co-sponsors with the United
States, the news agency added.
</P>
<P>
He expressed Russia's appreciation of Egypt's role in helping
push forward the peace process for the realization of a just and
comprehensive peace between Arab countries and Israel.
</P>
<P>
Egypt has intensified diplomatic efforts in the past week, in an
attempt to find "creative ideas" to help bring together the
Palestinians and Israelis.
</P>
<P>
Egypt was the first Arab state to sign a peace treaty with
Israel. 
</P>
