<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Kids Killed, 1 Injured in Explosion in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Three children were killed and
another one injured Tuesday afternoon in a mine or shell explosion
in south Lebanon, ANN television station reported.
</P>
<P>
Witness said the kids were playing near a former Israeli
position at the village of Braishit in south Lebanon. "They found a
metal and picked it up to see it, then the mine or a shell
exploded," said a boy who saw the tragedy.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of the children and the injured have been sent to the
hospital in the city of Tyre.
</P>
<P>
So far, nine people were killed and more than 50 others wounded,
mostly children, by mines or suspected shells in the Israeli-
vacated south Lebanon since it withdrew its troops on May 24 after
a 22-year occupation.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese military has warned people not to touch suspected
objects and drive on unpaved roads in the south.
</P>
<P>
The Ukrainian mine-cleaning unit serving in the United Nations
Interim Force in Lebanon (UNIFIL) complained that the maps if
minefields in south Lebanon provided by Israel is inaccurate.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that Israel left behind more than 130,000 mines,
only a small amount of which have been removed. Even worse, many
places in the area have also been mined during the 1975-1990 civil
war in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
