<HEADLINE> National Solidarity Fund Better Collected in 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A total of 242 billion lei
were collected at the National Solidarity Fund over August 1999-
July 2000, with 214 billion lei in the first seven months of 2000,
informed the Romanian Labor and Social Protection Ministry on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The fund's money is used for programs focused on the social
protection. One of the destinations of the money was a 25 percent
indexation of additional child benefit for families with two or
more children: around 141 billion lei for around 950,000 families.
</P>
<P>
The money was used also for the indexation of grants for
students, coverage of expenditures made by orphanages and old-age
houses. Moreover, the fund granted emergency aids and solidarity
allowances for the poorest families.
</P>
<P>
The Fund, administrated by the Labor Ministry, was set up in
1999 and its main source remains the social stamp on gambling,
worth 5 percent of the price of every participation in TV inter-
active games and 10 percent for the other types of games. Over 500
companies currently operate various types of gambling: casinos,
lotteries, contests on television and pooled wagering on sport.
</P>
<P>
Other source is represented by a 1 percent tax on the value of
imported new vehicles with at least 2,000 cc as well as of the
value of the new house structures on the issuance of the building
license for dwellings with an area of at least 250 sq.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
