<HEADLINE> 9 Killed, 6 Seriously Injured in Traffic Accident in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Nine people were killed and six
others seriously injured on Tuesday in a road accident in southern
Egypt, the country's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place when a minibus crashed head-on into a
small truck on a highway in the governorate of Minya, 220
kilometers south of Cairo, the news agency quoted an official at
the Interior Ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
A 22-year-old soldier, a teacher and five peasants aged between
40 and 60 were among the dead along with the two drivers, when the
small bus tried to overtake a car ahead of it, the official said on
customary condition of anonymity.
</P>
<P>
Traffic accidents are common in Egypt, where local newspapers
dub rural highways "roads of death," largely because of reckless
driving. Official figures show that about 3,000 people die in road
accidents each year in Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
