<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greek PM Sends Letter of Condolences Over Kursk Incident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Greek Prime Minister Costas
Simitis Tuesday sent a letter of condolences to Russian President
Vladimir Putin over the sinking of the Russian nuclear submarine
Kursk and the loss of its 118 crew.
</P>
<P>
Confirming this at a press briefing, Greek government
spokesman Dimitris Reppas said that Simitis expressed his grief
for the perished Russian sailors and condolences to their families
and relatives.
</P>
<P>
The Russian nuclear-powered submarine went down to sea when it
was participating in a military exercise in the Barents Sea on
August 12. All the 118 sailors on board were declared dead Monday
following several days of futile rescue efforts.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the incident remains unclear. 
</P>
</TEXT>
