<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Asks OPEC to Produce More Oil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The European Union on Tuesday
asked the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) to
increase production of oil so as to bring down the price.
</P>
<P>
A European Commission spokesman told the press that Loyola de
Palacio, EU energy commissioner, had telephoned OPEC President Ali
Rodriguez to ask the Venezuelan oil minister to try to bring down
the oil price.
</P>
<P>
The Central American country is now holding the rotating
presidency of the OPEC that has a quota system for oil production
for its member countries.
</P>
<P>
"The EU asked Venezuela to try and moderate their stance on the
oil price and to have a more reasonable price," said the spokesman,
who added that the 15-nation European bloc would like to see the
price of crude oil at around 25 U.S. dollars a barrel.
</P>
<P>
Crude oil has been trading of late at a 10-year high of close
to 30 dollars a barrel.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman for the commission, the executive body of the
European Union, said that the union was working with the United
States to coordinate efforts aimed at bringing down the price of
crude oil on the international market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
