<HEADLINE> Indian President Condoles Death Of Russian Sailors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Indian President Kocheril
Raman Narayanan Tuesday said that he was shocked to know about the
death of 118 sailors aboard the Russian submarine "Kursk" which
sank in the Barents Sea under tragic circumstances in spite of all
efforts to rescue them.
</P>
<P>
In a condolence message to Russian President Vladimir Putin,
Narayanan said he learnt of the news of the tragedy befalling the
Russian Navy on August 12 with great pain and sorrow.
</P>
<P>
"On behalf of the people of India and on my own behalf, I would
like to extend our sincere, heartfelt condolences to the family
members of the crew, the people of Russian Federation and to your
excellency," he said in the message. 
</P>
