<HEADLINE> Moravcova and Martikan Lead Slovak Gold Medal Hopes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRATISLAVA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Swimmer Martina Moravcova and
canoeist Michal Martikan lead Slovakia's Olympic gold medal hopes
in a 129-member team named on Tuesday for the Sydney Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
American-based Moravcova won gold, silver and bronze medals at
the European swimming championships in Helsinki in July.
</P>
<P>
She took gold in the 100 meters butterfly, silver in the 100m
and 200m freestyle and bronze in the 50m butterfly. Martikan won
the men's Canadian canoe singles title at the 1996 Atlanta Games.
</P>
<P>
Among other Slovak medal hopes are tennis players Karol Kucera
and Dominik Hrbaty and shooter Jozef Gonci. 
