<HEADLINE> U.S., Syrian FMs Discuss Mideast Peace on Phone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Foreign Minister Faruk
Shareh and United States Secretary of State Madeleine Albright held
a phone conversation Monday night on ways to revive the faltering
Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Shareh was quoted by the Syrian News Agency as highlighting the
Arab and Syrian stand which calls for Israeli pullout from the
Golan Heights of Syria and Arab East Jerusalem it seized in the
1967 Mideast war.
</P>
<P>
Shareh visited Saudi Arabia and Egypt over the past couple of
days for talks with senior officials of the two countries on the
latest developments in the region, the Middle East peace process
and means of resuming Syrian-Israeli negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian-Israeli negotiations were resumed in Washington last
December after a four-year suspension, but broke down once again in
January. 
