<HEADLINE> Myanmar-Lao Joint Commission Meets in Yangon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Joint Commission for
Bilateral Cooperation of Myanmar and Laos held its fifth meeting
here Tuesday, state-run Radio Myanmar reported Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
Attending the meeting were Myanmar commission, led by Foreign
Minister U Win Aung, and Lao commission, headed by visiting Deputy
Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Somsavat Lengsavad.
</P>
<P>
The joint commission discussed promotion of the existing
traditional friendship and bilateral cooperation as well as
regional and international issues.
</P>
<P>
Shortly after the meeting, First Secretary of the Myanmar State
Peace and Development Council Lieutenant-General Khin Nyunt met
with Somsavad who arrived here on Sunday for the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The fourth meeting was held in Vientiane in March last year
when Khin Nyunt visited Laos, during which the two countries'
foreign ministers signed an agreement on preventing trafficking of
drugs and psychotropic substances, and on controlling banned
chemical substances. 
