<HEADLINE> World Refugee Population Increases by 1.6 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The global refugee population
has increased by some 1.6 percent to reach 11.7 million by the end
of 1999, said a report by the Office of the United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR).
</P>
<P>
Asia hosts the largest share, with 41 percent, followed by
Africa (30.2 percent), Europe (22.3 percent), North America (5.4
percent), Oceania (0.6 percent) and Latin America and the
Caribbean (0.5 percent), said the report. 
</P>
