<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romanian, Hungarian Researchers Find Remedy Against Cancer: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A group of Romanian and
Hungarian researchers have discovered a remedy against certain
types of cancer, based on light water, the local daily newspaper
Curentul reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Light water is a secondary product obtained after removal of
tritium from heavy water.
</P>
<P>
The researchers found that the water of the human tissues
affected by malignant tumors have very high levels of deuterium.
By implementing the reverse process, the researchers gave patients
light water and pharmaceutical compounds made from it.
</P>
<P>
Results were impressive, with tumors not only being stopped,
but also cured, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Researchers of the National Development Institute for Cryogenic
and Isotopic Technologies based in Ramnicu Valcea of central
Romania, along with a team of Hungarian researchers, have obtained
a license for the product, which has already been sold and used
successfully, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Ramnicu Valcea Institute is one of only four research
centers worldwide that deal in recovering tritium from heavy water.
It produces light water in large amounts, at prices lower than the
other three institutes.
</P>
<P>
After forging an agreement with the Hungarian side, the Ramnicu
Valcea Institute grossed more than 700 million U.S. dollars from
exports of light water alone in nearly one year.
</P>
<P>
At last year's invention shows in Brussels and Geneva, the
institute was awarded 17 medals, including seven golds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000822.0067 </DOCNO>
