<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A unified Olympic team will
represent the formally divided country of Bosnia-Herzegovina, the
Bosnian Olympic Committee announced in Sarajevo on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Nine competitors, seven coaches and three members of the
organizational team from both the Muslim-Croat federation and the
Bosnian Serb republic -- the two autonomous regions that comprise
Bosnia since the civil war ended in 1995 -- will travel to Sydney
and compete in athletics, judo, shooting and swimming.
</P>
<P>
The size of the delegation could grow, depending on whether
other athletes qualify.
</P>
<P>
Having Bosnia's Muslims, Serbs and Croats now competing under a
common Bosnian flag in Sydney, Australia, is a proud success of
the Bosnian Olympic Committee.
</P>
<P>
"We have promoted sports without discrimination in harmony with
the Olympic spirit and understanding among people and ethnic
groups within Bosnia-Herzegovina," Bosnian Olympic Committee
president Bogic Bogicevic said. 
