<HEADLINE> China Stresses Plant Quarantine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Increased plant quarantine plays
an increasingly important role in guaranteeing China's safe
agricultural production and foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
According to a national plant quarantine conference, which
opened here today, quarantine departments across the country
examined 3,200 batches of imported seeds and 4.23 million tons of
plant products in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Plant diseases and insect pests brought along with imported
products have caused great losses to China's agricultural
production in recent years, said Chen Mengshan, an official with
the Ministry of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
China has promulgated a series of quarantine laws and
regulations, with quarantine departments located across the
country, doing on-the-spot inspections at plant production bases,
Chen said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past several years, quarantine departments have
succeeded in stopping the importation of diseased seeds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
