<HEADLINE> Official on Reform of Personnel System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- As China is entering a new stage
in its socialist modernization drive, the key for realizing the
goals set at the 15th Congress of the Communist Party of China (
CPC), is to produce an army of top-notch cadres.
</P>
<P>
Reforms of the cadres and personnel system must keep up with
the times, said a leading official with Organization Department of
the CPC Central Committee today when commenting on the recently
issued guideline on the reform of the cadres and personnel system.
</P>
<P>
The reform echoes the call by cadres and ordinary people who
are dissatisfied at corruption in personnel management, the
official said.
</P>
<P>
Along with the initial establishment of China's socialist
market economy, people's sense of democracy and rule of law is
increasing and the people have participated in personnel affairs
at a higher level, the official noted, adding that the guideline
is a general plan for the reform of personnel.
</P>
<P>
The guideline has set the basic goals, guiding principles and
basic demands and measures for deepening the personnel system
reform, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
The official listed the main tasks of the reform as follows:
</P>
<P>
-- To let more cadres be publicly selected and taking over
positions via competition;
</P>
<P>
-- To find ways for both promotion and demotion;
</P>
<P>
-- To make new progress in the exchange of officials between
different localities;
</P>
<P>
-- To strengthen supervision over the selection and appointment
of officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
