<HEADLINE> New York Liberty Rolls to WNBA Finals against Comets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The New York Liberty beat
Cleveland Rockers 81-67 Monday evening to advance to the WNBA
Championship Series against three-time titlists Houston Comets.
</P>
<P>
The Liberty, who outscored the Rockers 33-5 in the first 11
minutes at its Madison Square Garden, will ride a home court 13-
game winning streak into the opening game Thursday of the best-of-
three final against Comets.
</P>
<P>
Although the Comets hold home-court advantage, New York coach
Richie Adubato said of the opportunity to start at home, "It is
imperative that we win it."
</P>
<P>
New York has unfinished business with the Comets who have
denied them the title twice before. The Comets took last year's
third and decisive game 59-47 after earning the first of their
three successive crowns by topping New York 65-51 in the
Championship game in 1997.
</P>
<P>
"You've got to do a million and one things right to beat them,"
said Liberty's Teresa Weatherspoon, "They've won three
championships in a row. We've got to respect that but not fear
that."
</P>
<P>
New York used a sizzling start to dispatch Cleveland who owned
the league's worst record last year at 7-25 but improved to 17-15
to complete a remarkable turnaround and reach the postseason.
</P>
<P>
The Liberty whipped the home crowd into a frenzy by building a
33-5 cushion from 3-3 and 10-5 when the Rockers went the next 7:39
without a point before Tricia Bader drained a three-pointer, and
went on to a 46-27 halftime lead.
</P>
<P>
The Championship Finals will start in New York on Thursday
before the Comets hold the second game on Saturday, and possibly
on Sunday should two teams tied the scoreboard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
