<HEADLINE> Philippines to Host Asian Junior Baseball Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines will host the
first Asian Junior Nankyu Baseball Invitational Tournament which
will be held here on August 26 to 30.
</P>
<P>
Jointly organized by the Philippine Tot Baseball Foundation (
PTBF) and the Japan-based International Boys Nankyu Baseball
Association, the event for boys aged from 14 to 16 will be
participated in by two teams from Singapore and a team each from
Japan, Chinese-Taipei and the Philippines.
</P>
