<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hainan Strives to Protect Coral Reef </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, August 22 (Xinhua) -- This island province of Hainan
has been increasing patrol on the sea to curb random exploitation
of coral reefs in the South China Sea.
</P>
<P>
Relevant departments have also joined hands in closing markets
for trading of coral reefs across the province and shutting down
lime kilns which depend on coral reefs for raw materials, said
Jiang Zelin, head of the Hainan Provincial Bureau of Marine
Fishery.
</P>
<P>
China's corals and coral reefs are mainly distributed among
archipelago such as Nansha, Zhongsha and Xisha in South China Sea,
as well as in offshore areas along the coast of Hainan Island.
Local farmers usually use explosives to blast coral reefs and use
raw materials for making handicraft or producing lime.
</P>
<P>
A joint team organized recently by the province to deal with
acts in violation with regulations to protect marine wildlife and
coral reef resources found that 80 percent of the coral reefs in
the offshore areas around Hainan Island have been destroyed in
varying degrees.
</P>
<P>
The area of coral reefs along the coast of Hainan has shrunk to
22,200 hectares, down by 55 percent according to comparable figure
in the 1960s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
