<HEADLINE> Tianjin Port Builds Key Navigational Lane </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Construction started today on a
major navigational channel at Tianjin port, the largest in north
China.
</P>
<P>
According to a port official, the construction of the channel,
which is designed to accommodate 100,000-ton cargo ships, will be
completed in August next year.
</P>
<P>
The current channel of the port is 28.1 km long, 12 meters deep
and 180 meters wide, the official said, adding that the new
channel will be 28.8 km long, 15 meters deep and 200 meters wide.
</P>
<P>
The construction will involve a total investment of 168 million
yuan (about 20.25 million U.S. dollars), he added. 
</P>
