<HEADLINE> China Develops New Hacker-Proof Software </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Founder Electronic
Co., Ltd. here today launched its anti-hacker technological
solution at the on-going World Computer Congress (WCC).
</P>
<P>
Company representative Zou Wei said that the new anti-hacker
software does not bear any IP address on the Internet as similar
softwares do. Therefore, it cannot be discovered by hackers.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the software does not require any adjustment
of computer setups once it is installed.
</P>
<P>
Zou said that the packet filter III technology that his company
developed has already been approved by the Ministry of Public
Security of China and will be put into commercial production soon.
</P>
<P>
According to sources with WCC, software research institutes and
companies in other countries are also working on similar
technologies. However, Beijing Founder Electronic is the first one
to commercialize the patent.
</P>
<P>
The trademarked software SHARKS developed by the company has
already been used on the website highlighting Beijing's bid to
host the 2008 Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Zou said that SHARKS can effectively nip all types of DDoS
attacks.
</P>
<P>
SHARKS also offers an all-in-one solution to Internet companies
in terms of total security of website, reliable non-stop platform,
scaleable infrastructure and secure remote management. 
</P>
</TEXT>
