<HEADLINE> Cheng Kejie's Appeal Rejected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Higher People's
Court today rejected Cheng Kejie's appeal during a second public
hearing.
</P>
<P>
Cheng was found guilty of accepting 44 million yuan of bribes,
in collaboration with his mistress Li Ping.
</P>
<P>
On July 31, the former vice-chairman of the Standing Committee
of the National People's Congress, was sentenced to death with all
political rights deprived, according to a verdict passed by the
Beijing No.1 Intermediate People's Court.
</P>
<P>
The higher court came to the conclusion that Cheng has committed
severe crimes for taking huge bribes, alone or in collaboration
with Li Ping, by using his positions as the regional government
head and deputy secretary of the regional Party committee.
</P>
<P>
But Cheng and his counsel did not give any new evidence during
the second appeal. The death sentence should be approved by the
Supreme People's Court before Cheng can be executed, according to
China's Criminal Procedural Law. 
</P>
