<HEADLINE> Typhoon Bilis Approaching Taiwan, Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Typhoon Bilis is approaching
Taiwan and Fujian provinces in southeast China, according to the
Chinese Central Meteorological Station.
</P>
<P>
At 17:00 today, the center of the typhoon had moved to the sea
area 160 km southeast of Taidong, Taiwan, at 22.0 north and 122.4
east.
</P>
<P>
The typhoon is expected to move northwestward at 20 km per hour
and to land on the eastern coast of Taiwan tonight and on the
coastal area of Fujian tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
The sea areas affected will experience heavy winds ranging from
moderate gales to hurricanes. Taiwan, most part of Fujian and
Zhejiang provinces, and eastern parts of Guangdong and Jiangxi
provinces and the whole Hainan Province are expected to have
rainstorms or heavy rains. 
</P>
