<HEADLINE> Team to Check Implementation of Criminal Procedural Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC) plans to send an inspection team
to implement the Criminal Procedural Law in six provincial
administrative areas between September and October.
</P>
<P>
The team held its first plenary meeting here today. Li Peng,
chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, attended and spoke at the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
The inspection is aimed at pressing local judicial departments
to punish criminals.
</P>
<P>
During their tour, the team will check activities of police and
judicial units on a number of issues such as detention of suspects
by police and judicial departments; self-examination on torture by
police and judicial departments; arrests by procuratorates; and
reduction of jail terms and paroles granted by courts.
</P>
<P>
The team, which is divided into six groups, will be headed by
Cao Zhi, vice chairman of the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
In addition, standing committees of provincial people's
congresses of Hebei, Jilin, Shandong, Yunnan and Qinghai and the
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region will be authorized by the NPC
Standing Committee to check the matter in their own localities.
They will hand over their inspection reports to the General Office
of the NPC Standing Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
