<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Prepares for Census Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A comprehensive census will be
conducted in the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) in
August next year and a ten-day trial census will begin Wednesday,
official sources said at a press conference Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"Both the formal census and trial census need the support and
cooperation of residents, who are expected to provide accurate
data to complete the questionnaires," said Lok Kit Sim, acting
director of the Statistics and Census Services of the Macao SAR
government.
</P>
<P>
The census will be the first since Macao's return to the
motherland in last December. Census was carried out for the first
time in 1867 and 13 censuses have been conducted in Macao about
every ten years, with the latest one in 1991.
</P>
<P>
To ensure the success of the census next year, a trial census
will be held from August 23 to September 1 in a designated typical
area. And 210 middle school and university students have been
trained to conduct the trial census well.
</P>
<P>
The surveyors and other people related in the census have
signed written promise to keep secret the personal data of
residents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
