<HEADLINE> HK Stocks End Up 0.95 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks ended up
Tuesday, thanks to the strong performance of banking stocks on the
optimism about the stable U.S. interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index climbed 166.80 points, or 0.95 percent, to
finish Tuesday's session at 17,668.28.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 10.837 billion HK dollars (1.389 billion U.S.
dollars), as against to Monday's 9.148 billion HK dollars (1.173
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corporation (HSBC) Holdings,
whose shares reached a high of 113.50 HK dollars (14.5 U.S.
dollars), helped the gains of the Hang Seng Index. The stock has
risen over 30 percent in the past three months, due to the
expectations that the U.S. Federal Reserve would leave the
interest rates unchanged in the short term.
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices, Finance and Property gained 2.97
percent and 2.18 percent, while Utilities and Commerce &AMP; Industry
lost 0.45 percent and 0.40 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares ended mixed with the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index down 0.60 percent and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corp Index up 0.55 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index and Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index fell 1.
03 percent and 1.23 percent.
</P>
<P>
The blue chips went up 66.63 points, or 0.38 percent, to open
at 17,568.11 Tuesday. The stock prices kept on the rise and closed
the morning session at 17,610.50. 
</P>
</TEXT>
