<HEADLINE> HK Sees 0.9 Percent in Population Growth Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The population of Hong Kong
reached 6,782,100, in the mid-2000, according to the provisional
figure released by the Census and Statistics Department of Hong
Kong Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
There was an increase of 61,400 persons as compared with the
mid-1999 population, representing a growth rate of 0.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
There were 51,400 births and 33,800 deaths in Hong Kong in the
past year. The natural growth thus amounted to 17,600, accounting
for 29 percent of the population growth.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, the net movement showed a net inflow of
some 43,800 persons, constituting 71 percent of the population
growth.
</P>
<P>
Of the 6,782,100 persons within the mid-2000 Hong Kong
population, 6,593,400 were usual residents and 188,700 were mobile
residents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
