<P>
The computers and printers, totaling 356, were donated by
central government departments.
</P>
<P>
Deng Pufang, chairman of the China Disabled Persons' Federation,
said at the ceremony that computers are becoming more important
and friendly to the disabled. The donated machines will be of much
help to the disabled in poor areas.
</P>
<P>
Since the federation initiated the donation activity three
months ago, a total of 538 computers and printers were donated to
the federation. Of which, 356 were tested good and will be sent to
poor and backward regions to help the education and vocational
training of the handicapped.
</P>
<P>
Deng asked the disabled federations at all levels to properly
manage the computers and printers, and bring them into full use
for the disabled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
