<HEADLINE> Share Prices Edge Up on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) gained 9.82 points to
end at 2,210.51 points in light trading.
</P>
<P>
The market volume increased to 329.10 million units worth 497.
65 million Singapore dollars (about 290.02 million U.S. dollars).
Gainers outpaced losers by 225 to 81 with 227 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was the 16.32 million parcel by NW Tech which
was transacted at 0.58 Singapore dollars per unit. It was followed
by ITech Grp which had 14.67 million shares traded. Cytech was the
next with 13.35 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Asean topped the day's gainers rising by 90 cents to close at 9.
80 U.S. dollars. DBS put on 60 cents to finish at 23.10 Singapore
dollars. SIA 200 added 50 cents to end at 19.10 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Venture headed the descent of the day sinking 50 cents to close
at 22.00 Singapore dollars. Chartered slipped 30 cents to finish
at 14.60 Singapore dollars. Times Pub retreated 22 cents to end at
3.76 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market ended in lackluster trading as cautious
sentiment prevailed over the market ahead of the U.S. Federal
Reserve's decision making on interest rate later Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
They noted that property stocks, led by heavyweight City
Developments, rose as investors held on to hopes that the Fed will
not raise rates.
</P>
