<HEADLINE> Liverpool Escapes Fine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Liverpool will not be fined
despite having two players sent off in their 2-0 defeat by Arsenal,
the Football Association (FA) said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
New FA rules say clubs will be fined 25,000 pounds (37,000 U.S.
dollars) if they receive six cautions in one match.
</P>
<P>
Liverpool picked up six cards during the English premier league
defeat at Highbury on Monday, including four yellow and two reds
for Gary McAllister and Dietmar Hamann.
</P>
<P>
However, only five players were cautioned because Hamann
received two yellow cards.
</P>
<P>
An FA spokesman said: "For the fine to be administered, six
different names have to be taken by the referee."
</P>
<P>
Arsenal's Patrick Vieira was sent off for the second time in
two games in the 73rd minute of the match. 
</P>
