<HEADLINE> Shenzhen B-share Market Down at Tuesday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen B-share market
index slumped 3.34 points or 2.47 percent to 131.65 points on
Tuesday, amid unusually chopping and heavy trading.
</P>
<P>
Turnover broadened to 554.57 million Hong Kong dollars, which
was 235.76 million Hong Kong dollars or 73.95 percent more than
the total on Monday, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line
financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The merger speculation of the Class A and Class B shares had
driven the index to a peak of 141.23 points in early afternoon,
the top level in almost three years. However, the market suddenly
reversed its courses on late-day profit-taking that had
significantly cut into the impressive gains, dragging the index
into the red.
</P>
<P>
Market breadth turned decisively negative. Losers beat gainers
by 47 to 8, with 1 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Benelux Ent rose 4.76 percent to 3.08 Hong Kong dollars, while
Zhonglu climbed up 2.49 percent to 3.29 Hong Kong dollars.
</P>
<P>
Hefei Meiling fell 8.73 percent to 2.30 Hong Kong dollars,
while Nanshan Power lost 8.60 percent to 3.40 Hong Kong dollars.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts predicted that the market's latest aggressive
performance is likely to be hurdled in the coming sessions as it
is poised to meet resistance resulted from profit-taking.
</P>
</TEXT>
