<HEADLINE> Chinese Treasuries Stable on Tuesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese treasuries stood stable
on Tuesday while the total transaction value contracted by 244
million yuan to 1.76 billion yuan as the domestic stock market
recorded a broad-based slump since August 7.
</P>
<P>
Bond 000896 jumped the most to 123.79 yuan, 0.17 percent higher
than yesterday, pressing the yield down 0.06 percentage points to
2.94 percent, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line
financial and securities company.
</P>
<P>
Bond 009908 picked up 0.04 percent to end at 103.04 yuan with
the yield down 0.02 percentage points to 3.29 percent. The bond is
still the most active performer on the market.
</P>
<P>
The new floating-rate 010004, whose coupon rate is 2.87 percent
this year, stayed stable at 104.52 yuan today after yesterday's
big gains.
</P>
<P>
Trade volume of three-day, seven-day, 14-day and 28-day
repurchasing transactions shrank by 71 percent to 2.31 billion
yuan compared with the last close. However, the interest rate of
the three-day repurchasing agreement gained 0.41 percentage points
to 2.99 percent. 
