<HEADLINE> Chinese Fund Market Remains Steady Tuesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese securities
investment fund market remained steady to stick to its recent
tight ranges despite an overall slump on the stock market today.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Market Fund Index edged down 1.62 points or 0.15
percent to 1076.13 points, while the Shenzhen Market Fund Index
shed 9.32 points or 0.85 to 1085.19 points, according to Homeway,
China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Of the 30 funds, gainers broke even with losers.
</P>
<P>
Of the 22 discounted funds, things were getting better after a
period of correction. On the winners' side, Fund Jingbo and Fund
Hansheng rose 0.88 percent and 0.85 percent respectively. Fund
Jinhong, Fund Yulong and Fund Tongyi fell by more than 1 percent
to trim their gains last week.
</P>
<P>
The underlying tone for the discount funds turned somehow
bullish as the interim reports, due out in the next eight trading
sessions, are widely expected to show favorable results.
</P>
<P>
Fund Handing was again stuck in its price ceiling of 1.77 yuan
soon after opening bell before it closed at 1.71 yuan. 34.21
million fund units were traded, the largest turnover since the
fund was listed last week on the Shanghai Stock Exchange,
indicating the fund was subject to selling pressure. 
</P>
