<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Bounces to Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 22 (Xinhua) - The Australian sharemarket
overcame early weakness to bounce to a record high Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The S&AMP;P/ASX 200 closed 14.5 points higher at 3353.4.
</P>
<P>
Overall 498.74 million shares were traded worth 1.476 billion
Australian dollars (870.84 U.S. dollars). There were 711 rising
stocks, 763 falling and 611 were steady.
</P>
<P>
Financial services company Perpetual Trustees climbed to a
record high closing at 31.00 Australian dollars, up 1.35 dollars,
after announcing a 31 percent rise in annual net profit.
</P>
<P>
Kerry Packer's Publishing &AMP; Broadcasting added 12.9 cents to 14.
45 Australian dollars. News Corp's ordinary shares fell to an
intraday low of 22.02 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Telstra shares fell eight cents to 7.20 and the Second-ranked
telco Cable &AMP; Wireless Optus ended down eight cents to 4.47
Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the resources sector, BHP lost 25 cents to 19.35 Australian
dollars, Rio Tinto gained 11 cents to 26.66 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The rising oil price sent oil stocks higher, Woodside soared 71.
4 cents to 14.394 Australian dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
