<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index shed 1.51
points to 807.89, the all-share Emas Index eased 0.65 of a point
to 201.63, the Industrial Index lost 6.91 points to 1,438.57 and
the Second Board Index fell 1.03 points to 209.96.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 372 to 198 while 201 counters were
unchanged and 230 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's total turnover increased to 97.656 million shares
worth 253.207 million ringgit (about 66.63 million U.S. dollars)
from 72.364 million shares valued at 229.640 million ringgit (
about 60.43 million U.S. dollars) on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
