<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Stronger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar climbed
back to 59 U.S. cents Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the close the Australian dollar was at 59.03 U.S. cents,
from 58.98 on the previous day.
</P>
<P>
Traders believed the U.S. central bank would not raise interest
rates in its monetary policy meeting Tuesday night and This could
turn the interest rate gap in favor of Australian dollar. 
</P>
