<HEADLINE> Hizb, Al-Badar Claim Responsibility of Landmine Blast in Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Hizbul Mujahideen and Al-
Badar Mujahideen Tuesday claimed responsibility of the landmine
attack on Monday on Indian troops' patrol vehicle in Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
The Hizb in a statement claimed the death toll of the Indian
troops at 8 while the Al-Badar put the toll at 12.
</P>
<P>
The two groups, however, made similar claim of using remote
control to detonate the device and blew up the jeep in Baramula
district.
</P>
</TEXT>
