<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia's Putin to Be in Murmansk for Kursk Mourning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Vladimir Putin
will fly to Murmansk, the base of the Northern Fleet, on Tuesday
afternoon to pay his final respects to the crew of the sunken
nuclear submarine Kursk, said the Kremlin.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Tuesday, Putin declared Wednesday a day of national
mourning for the submarine's crew.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, the Russian president, also commander-in-chief of
the country's armed forces, will sail to the area where the sub
sank. Memorial ceremonies will be held on fleet vessels. According
to a naval tradition, flowers and floral wreaths will be thrown
into the water, the presidential press service said.
</P>
<P>
The Kremlin indicated that Putin might meet with relatives and
friends of the submarine crew. Top Defense Ministry officials are
expected to accompany the president on his trip to the Northern
Fleet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
