<HEADLINE> Share Prices Soar in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices rose sharply in Tokyo
Tuesday on active buying of semiconductor-related issues.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange surged 414.56 points, or 2.58
percent, from Monday's close to end at 16,454.74.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, advanced 21.33 points, or 1.45 percent, to 1,
494.78.
</P>
<P>
Toshiba Corp. on Monday announced an upward revision of its
consolidated sales forecast for the first half of the current
business year, encouraging investors to buy other semiconductor
makers, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section grew to 560.60 million shares
from Monday's 422.20 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Toshiba was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
The paper, mining and real estate sectors marked sharp gains,
while banks and the rubber sector were also higher.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers outnumbered
losers 910 to 334, while 154 issues closed unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
