<HEADLINE> Shanghai B-share Market Down At Tuesday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai B-share market
index plunged 3.67 points, or 4.41 percent, to 79.40 points on
Tuesday, coming off its intraday high of 85.64 points in early
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 95.32 million U.S. dollars, which was 26.99 U.S.
dollars or 39.50 percent more than Monday's total, according to
Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory
company.
</P>
<P>
After posting nice gains in the early morning, the market
succumbed to abrupt selling pressure in the late afternoon and did
not manage to recover, as profit-takers mounted up to drag most
stocks down significantly after the week-long aggressive advance.
</P>
<P>
Losers overwhelmingly beat gainer by 47 to 5, with 3 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Tientsin Marine climbed 5.15 percent to 0.408 U.S. dollars,
while ST Steel Tube rose 8.25 percent to 0.420 US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Autom Instrum fell 9.47 percent to 0.306 US dollars, while
Dahua Chemical lost 9.37 percent to 0.290 US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts predicted that as for tomorrow, more cautious
trading is widely expected as many believe that the near-term
direction seems not very clear and besides, the market needs time
to consolidate.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
