<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Market Dives at Tuesday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Composite Index
dived sharply in the last half an hour to the intraday nadir of
2074.7 points, after it hit a lifetime high 2114.52 points on
opening bell.
</P>
<P>
For the most time of the day, the market was hovering above
the 2110-point level, before the tone turned suddenly bearish
toward the close.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 14.93 billion yuan, which was 8.4 percent less
than Monday's 16.3 billion yuan, according to Homeway, China's
leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The sharp slide was mostly attributed to profit-taking, which
had been mounting up in the past seven weeks, during which the
Shanghai composite index continued to rewrite its high records.
</P>
<P>
Technically speaking, given it had accumulated so much gains,
the market did need to correct the upward trend with the 10-day
moving average its the first line of support.
</P>
<P>
Hainan Lawron Development Co.,Ltd was the top gainer today
with its price up 9.92 percent to 20.06 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
Chengdu Gongyi Metallurgy Co.,Ltd was the biggest loser today.
Its price shed 7.23 percent to 11.93 yuan per share, hit by profit
taking.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts predicted that the A-share market is likely
to rebound tomorrow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
