<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Stock Market Plunges at Tuesday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen Composite Index
closed at its intraday low of 632.99 points on Tuesday, shedding
10.78 points or 1.67 percent compared with the last close. The sub-
index closed at 4,941.32 points, losing 79.93 points or 1.59
percent.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 13.55 billion yuan, 15.2 percent less than Monday'
s 15.98 billion yuan, according to Homeway, China's leading on-
line financial and securities company.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen Composite Index touched a new record of 645.17
points when the market opened this morning. However, it headed
straightforward into the negative territory in the last half an
hour after hovering around 640 points for most of the day.
</P>
<P>
The sharp slide was mostly blamed for profit-taking, which
gained strength in the past seven weeks, when the Shenzhen
composite index kept rewriting its high records. On a technical
basis, the upward move looked poised to be corrected somehow with
the ten-day moving average seen as the first line of support.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong Jintai Developing Co., Ltd was the top gainer today
with its price up 5.65 percent to 17.75 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
Neimengu Hongfeng Industry Co., Ltd., was the biggest loser
today. Its price shed 9.98 percent to 19.3 yuan per share, hit by
profit taking.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts predicted that the A-share market is likely to
rebound tomorrow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
