<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's GDP Growth to Reach 6.5-7.0 Percent in 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's gross domestic product
GDP) growth is estimated to reach 6.5-7 percent in 2000, Vietnam's
official news agency VNA reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The growth will be one percent higher than the target set by
Vietnam's National Assembly, according to the Ministry of Planning
and Investment (MPI).
</P>
<P>
Vietnam registered a year-on-year increase of 6.2 percent in
GDP in the first six months of the year.
</P>
<P>
The MPI also forecast that Vietnam may be possible this year to
obtain increases of 5 percent in agriculture, forestry and
fisheries, 15 percent in industrial production, and 6 percent in
services, in comparison to the set targets of 3.3-4.0 percent, 10.
5-11.0 percent and 5.0-5.5 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Export turnover is estimated to reach a 17 percent increase
against the 11-12 percent targeted.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's state budget revenue is estimated at 77,500-78,500
billion Vietnamese dong (VND) (about 5.54-5.61 billion U.S.
dollars) in 2000, surpassing estimates by 3,000-4,000 billion VND
(about 214-285 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The total capital for socio-economic development may reach 125,
400 billion VND (about 8.96 billion U.S. dollars) this year, a 20.
6 percent increase over 1999. The target set for natural
population growth will be met at 1.53 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
