<HEADLINE> Shanghai Increases Computer Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's export of computers
and parts from January to July reached 1.4 billion U.S. dollars,
37.4 percent up from the same period of last year, according to
statistics from the customs.
</P>
<P>
Processing trade remained an overwhelming sector in the export
of computers, taking up 99 percent of the total volume.
</P>
<P>
The United States and the Netherlands were the two major export
destinations, followed by Japan and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded enterprises are major computer exporters,
totaling 1.34 billion U.S. dollars in volume.  
