<HEADLINE> ASEAN Countries Efforts to Eradicate Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The members countries of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) here Tuesday
started a three-day meeting aimed at drawing up a new poverty
eradication program.
</P>
<P>
Opening the meeting which attended by senior officials of the
10 member countries, Indonesian Coordinating Minister for Social
and Welfare and Poverty Eradication Basri Hasanuddin noted in his
address that poverty in the region needs greater attention and
must be uprooted soon.
</P>
<P>
"We must solve this problem if we plan to move ahead with
another development program," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the participants to produce a solution which
could be implemented by all ASEAN member countries.
</P>
<P>
"There must be a joint network on this (poverty eradication)
among ASEAN countries because the ASEAN must work together to
improve the peoples' welfare," Hasanuddin added.
</P>
<P>
Referring to Indonesia's poverty eradication program, the
minister said the central government has decided to give greater
authority to local governments in handling the people's problems.
</P>
<P>
"It is very effective because they (local governments) are the
institutions who know exactly what is going on in the society," he
said.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN is composed of Indonesia, Malaysia, Thailand, Singapore,
the Philippines, Brunei Darussalam, Cambodia, Laos, Myanmar and
Vietnam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
