<HEADLINE> Ugandan Government to Fund Dam Construction in Drought-hit Region  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Ugandan government has set
aside 3.4 billion Uganda shillings (2 million U.S. dollars) for
construction of water dams and valley tanks in Karamoja region
which has been hit by persisting drought this year.
</P>
<P>
