apologized to Karimojong for the neglect they have suffered under
successive governments.
</P>
<P>
"It's now significant that we want to apologize to the
Karimojong that for long they have not been part of Uganda's
development process," Kazibwe said last week.
</P>
<P>
The vice president was on a food security mobilization program
in Karamoja region following reports of famine there.
</P>
<P>
She visited Kailong valley dam, recently constructed by the
government at 500 million Uganda shillings which is part of a 3.4
billion shillings pledge to address Karamoja's long standing water
problem.
</P>
<P>
"If the government is to develop and modernize agriculture in
Karamoja, we must link the cow, water and the mother earth through
irrigation," said the vice president. 
