<HEADLINE> Van Roost Struggles to Advance at Pilot Pen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Dominique Van Roost of
Belgium struggled to advance Monday after she ousted Blugaria's
Magdalena Maleeva 7-6 (7-2), 6-4 in the first round of the Pilot
Pen WTA event in New Haven, Connecticut.
</P>
<P>
Van Roost, seeded sixth, survived two set points at 5-6 against
Maleeva, who beat Amanda Coetzer and Lindsay Davenport last week
in Montreal, before she swept the tiebreaker in the first set.
</P>
<P>
Fifth seed Coetzer of South Africa beat Slovakian qualifier
Karina Habsudova by exactly the same score.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, Russia's Elena Likhovtseva claimed an easy 6-
1, 6-3 win over Italian qualifier Tathiana Garbin to set up a
second meeting with top seed Venus Williams, and wild card entry
Kristina Brandi of the United States beat Luxembourg's Anne Kremer
to earn a clash with second seed Monica Seles. 
</P>
