<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Homes for Three Gorges Dam Immigrants (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The new town of Fengjie is made primarily by a stone-paved road
consisting of over a thousand steps, flanked on each side with two-
story buildings, the upper story for families and the lower for
bookstores, art galleries and other stores.
</P>
<P>
Actually, the road received the nickname "stone ladder" and
attracts quite a few visitors at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Different from the old towns, which habitually discharged
rubbish and wastewater directly into the Yangtze River, the new
town of Fengjie is equipped with various environmental protection
measures like a rubbish processing ground and sewage treatment
plant that entails new technology.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, clean energy like natural gas and liquefied petroleum
gas have replaced coal to become the major fuel sources.
</P>
<P>
Compared with Fengjie, the neighboring town of Yunyang is much
faster in getting up and running. Not only has its infrastructure
construction been completed, but local government and residents
have already begun to move in.
</P>
<P>
The old town of Yunyang used to have nearly 100 factories,
governmental agencies, schools, and about 30,000 residents along a
single street about 10 meters wide. By contrast, the new town has
been divided into different functional districts for residences,
culture, business and industry.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Chongqing alone has allocated 5 billion
yuan to build the new towns. Construction in most of these 13 new
towns is still in full swing.
</P>
<P>
Hopefully, local residents will move into their new homes next
year, as scheduled by the local government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
