<HEADLINE> East China City Opens Solo Art Show in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A painting and sculpture show
opened at the China National Gallery in this national capital to
mark the beginning of a six-day art show by schools from Changzhou
City, in eastern Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time that schools from a medium-sized city like
Changzhou have ever held a solo art exhibition, according to
official sources.
</P>
<P>
Local experts attributed it to the rapid economic development
of the city over the past two decades and the priority given by
local government to developing local education sector, including
the art education, to improve the quality of students in an all-
about way.
</P>
<P>
The show includes the painting exhibition and three concerts
held by a children's band from Changzhou, according to Wang Heming,
director of the city's education department. The band has visited
many foreign countries and regions and is called a "Young Friendly
Envoy", he said.
</P>
<P>
In Changzhou, a well-developed city in education, all local
schools there have opened art courses.  
</P>
