<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, August 22 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES -- Ice cream and other frozen desserts sales in the
United States totaled 11.5 billion U.S. dollars in 1999, up almost
3 percent from a year ago, a U.S. marketplace service reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The biggest seller in the frozen dessert category is packaged
ice cream which captured more than 52 percent of the market share
in 1999 with sales totaling 6 billion dollars, according to
MarkeResearch.com. Frozen novelties are second in sales with a 35
percent market share equaling 4.25 billion dollars in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Overall sales projections for ice cream and frozen novelties
will grow almost 8 percent between 1999 and 2004, when total sales
will approach 12.8 billion dollars. (US-Ice Cream)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SAN JOSE -- Representatives from nine Latin American coffee
producing countries will meet Wednesday in Costa Rica to discuss
the fall in coffee bean price at the international market.
</P>
<P>
The participants will discuss the measures needed to arrest the
fall, including cutting production, Secretary General of the
Coffee Producing Countries Association (CPCA), Roveiro Silva, said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The price fell to 78.4 dollars per sack last Friday, one of the
lowest in the last decades. (LAmerica-Coffee)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- The government is considering a proposal that
Thailand conduct counter-trade with oil producing countries in the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) and China in
purchasing petroleum products from these countries, the Thai News
Agency (TNA) reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The country's private sector has proposed that the government
negotiate with ASEAN oil producing countries, including Brunei,
Indonesia, and Malaysia for the purchase of oil at friendship
prices, or on a counter-trade basis, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The counter-trade, which can also be extended to China, should
mainly be focused on exports of Thai agricultural products in
exchange for gasoline and other petroleum products from these
countries, it added. (Thailand-ASEAN-Trade) 
