<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodian Airline Needs Restructuring: Senior Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As RAC jet spewed fuel moments before it was to take King
Norodom Sihanouk to China not long ago, Hun Sen fired RAC's top
officials immediately after the incident and appointed minister of
the cabinet Sok An as temporary chairman of RAC.
</P>
<P>
On August 16, a RAC plane was found technical trouble shortly
before taking-off and forced to cancel the flight.
</P>
<P>
It is high time for RAC to restructure, Sok An said.
</P>
<P>
"We need experience from big companies and human resources to
make this improvement," aimed at making RAC more competitive, the
cabinet minister was quoted as saying by the daily.
</P>
<P>
"Until today, (RAC) has not been strong and has not profited,"
he added. RAC has, in fact, lost at least 25 million U.S. dollars
in recent years, according to airline executives. 
</P>
