<DOCNO> XIE20000822.0265 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Human Error Blamed for Thai Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quoting nearly two-year findings of an inquiry team headed by
Thai Air Force Chief-of-Staff Therdsak Sajjarak, it said," the
pilots did not see the runway when the plane was approaching the
airport because of bad weather."
</P>
<P>
When the pilots saw the runway as the plane was very close to
the airport, they descended suddenly but the plane was heading for
the control tower. "So they abruptly turned the plane which
consequently lost its balance and crashed," the report said.
</P>
<P>
The probe team will discuss the conclusion of the investigation
Thursday, together with representatives of the air force, the
Aviation Department and the national airline, it said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, officials concerned met at the Transport Ministry
Monday, discussing plans on air safety, including a 2.9-billion-
baht (72 million U.S. dollars) project to enhance safety and
rescue measures. 
</P>
