<HEADLINE> Hungarian Customs Seizes 30 Kilograms of Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Hungarian customs officers had
seized 30 kilograms of heroin with a street value of 160 million
forints (559,440 U.S. dollars) in Nagylak bordering Romania, local
media reports said Monday.
</P>
<P>
During a customs inspection late Sunday night, the officers
found the drug, pressed into 58 packages, in the driver's cab and
toolbox of a Turkish container van heading for the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months of this year alone, Hungarian customs
officers seized 400 kilograms of drugs, compared with 200
kilograms for the whole of 1999. The largest haul in recent years
was made on May 28, when 169 kilograms of heroin were seized in
Nagylak with a street value of 895 million forints (3.1 million
dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
