<HEADLINE> Official Urges Developing West China by Science, Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
has stressed the importance of developing the economically
backward western part of the country by giving top priority to
developing science, technology and education.
</P>
<P>
He also emphasized the introduction of innovative conception,
new ways of thinking, updated mechanism and science and technology
in implementing the government's strategy to develop the
underdeveloped areas.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remarks during a study tour of Ningxia Hui and
Xinjiang Uygur autonomous regions, both in the northwest, from
August 14-21.
</P>
<P>
During his trip, the vice-premier talked with local leaders and
inspected a number of schools, research institutions, enterprises,
poverty-eradication projects, and water conservancy facilities.
</P>
<P>
He praised the efforts by local authorities to develop local
economy, consolidate unity among people of different ethnic groups,
and maintain social stability. All this has helped push ahead the
social progress in an all-about way, he said.
</P>
<P>
He called on the local people not to miss the historic
opportunities of launching the strategy to develop the west and
the new scientific and technological revolution in the new century.
Learning from the past, top priority must be given to developing
science, technology and education during the whole process of
developing the vast western areas, Li noted.
</P>
<P>
The development of the west calls for a high-quality personnel,
the development of science and technology, and the cultural and
ethic progress, he said.
</P>
<P>
The vice premier also demanded that local research and
educational sectors speed up their reforms to provide the west
with more technological achievements and professionals.
</P>
<P>
The central government and the developed eastern part of the
country will also give greater assistance to help develop the
educational sector in the west, Li stated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
