<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Higher People's
Court has today rejected Cheng Kejie's appeal during a public
hearing at the second instance trial, maintaining the verdict at
the first instance.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Kejie, former vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of
the National People's Congress, was sentenced to death with all
political rights deprived of permanently. He was found guilty of
accepting bribes totaling 44 million yuan, in collaboration with
his mistress Li Ping.
