<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico Seeks to Enhance Tourism Ties with Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The governor of the Mexican
Caribbean state of Quintana Roo, Joaquin Hendricks, said on Monday
that he intends to support tourism cooperation between Cuba and
Cancun.
</P>
<P>
The governor, who arrived on Sunday evening in Havana for a two-
day trip, will sign a cooperation accord with Cuba's minister of
tourism on exchanging travel information and publicity.
</P>
<P>
Cancun, in the state of Quintana Roo, receives 4 million
tourists per year, and is the greatest and most profitable tourist
resort in Mexico.
</P>
<P>
Cuba, on the other hand, received 1.6 million tourists last
year and expects to receive nearly 2 million visitors by the end
of 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
