<HEADLINE> Canadian PM Expresses Sadness at Russian Submarine Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien Monday expressed deep sadness at the news that there were
no survivors aboard the Russian submarine Kursk.
</P>
<P>
"Like people the world over, the hopes and prayers of Canadians
have been with the crew of the Kursk and their families as the
rescue effort unfolded. And we are deeply saddened at the news
that none of the crew is left alive," said the prime minister in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
The Russian military has confirmed that all the 118 crew aboard
Kursk died after the submarine went down to the bottom of the
Barents on August 12. 
</P>
</TEXT>
