<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IAAF Ban Christie and Fellows for Two Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The International Amateur Athletic
Federation (IAAF) banned on Monday former Olympic gold medalist
Linford Christie of Britain and fellow British athletes Doug
Walker and Gary Cadogan for two years.
</P>
<P>
The trio failed dope tests for the banned anabolic steroid
nandrolone in the space of four months in late 1998 and early 1999.
</P>
<P>
The British panel cleared the case but the decision was
overturned by the sport's ruling body IAAF in November, ordering
to set up their own arbitration panel to reconsider the case.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
