<HEADLINE> South American Players Stand Out in Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Foreign soccer players,
especially those from South America, were protagonists in the
elaboration of last week's soccer matches of the Winter 2000
Tournament of Mexicos premier league.
</P>
<P>
Foreign players scored 13 out of the total of 27 goals.
</P>
<P>
Irapuato took the lead of the league after winning over Pachuca
2-0 with goals from Argentinian Cristian Morales and Uruguayan
Martin Rodriguez.
</P>
<P>
Atlas from Guadalajara, led by an Argentinian world champion,
Antonio Lavolpe, won 3-2 over the mighty Cruz Azul with a last-
minute goal by Argentinian Hugo Castillo.
</P>
<P>
Brazlian Alessadnro Fernandes of Morelia, scored the only goal
in a game against Celaya, while Adelino Batista, also from Brazil,
gave a 1-0 victory to Leon over Guadalajara.
</P>
<P>
America won 2-1 over Necaxa with scores by Jose Luis Calderon
from Argentina, and excellent plays by the Colombians Frankie
Oveiedo and Leonardo Fabio. 
</P>
</TEXT>
