<HEADLINE> China's Software Firms Form National Alliance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 22 (Xinhua) -- China's information technology
(IT) companies involved in software development have set up a
national union to compete with foreign competitors in the near
future.
</P>
<P>
Allwin Software Union, a nationwide union of companies involved
in software development and production, as well as software system
integration and services, has been formed in northeast China's
Liaoning Province lately.
</P>
<P>
The union, initiated by NEU-Alpine, a leading Chinese software
firm based in Shenyang, capital of Liaoning Province, aims at
building a powerful IT coalition by inviting the participation of
software businesses across the country.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 800 software firms have joined the union over the past
10 months. Membership businesses of Allwin Software Union have
made sound profits with rich resources from the union as a strong
support.
</P>
<P>
Liu Jiren, chairman of the board of NEU-Alpine, said that the
establishment of Allwin Software Union is to unite domestic
software companies to compete with foreign competitors by making
better use of technology, management, operation and marketing
advantages from the individual firms.
</P>
<P>
NEU-Alpine, established in conjunction with Northeast
University's (NEU) software center, operates more than 30 Chinese
subsidiaries engaged in software development and marketing.
</P>
</TEXT>
