<HEADLINE> China To Auction A Holiday Resort </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A holiday resort at a famous
tourist attraction near China's largest city of Shanghai will be
auctioned off soon due to debt problems, according to an official
source.
</P>
<P>
The resort is in the Haoyun (Goodluck) Island in the Qiandaohu
Lake which attracts millions of visitors annually.
</P>
<P>
The resort includes some 10 villas and a large area of trees
and bamboo forests. It is the only place on the Haoyun Island
that visitors can stay overnight.
</P>
<P>
According to the source, this is the first time for the country
to auction a holiday resort at a famous tourist attraction.
</P>
<P>
The auction will be conducted by the Shanghai International
Commodity Auction Limited Company. 
