<HEADLINE> Cuba Announces State of Alert Caused by Hurricane Debby </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Cuban authorities decreed Tuesday
a state of alert for its eastern provinces of Holguin, Guantanamo
and Las Tunas, situated in Hurricane Debby's eventual path.
</P>
<P>
A note from Cuba's Civil Defense Staff declared an informative
phase for central Camaguey and Ciego de Avila provinces and kept
the same category for Granma and Santiago de Cuba.
</P>
<P>
The communique is asking organisms, social institutions and the
population to fulfill preventive measures oriented for a scourge
of this kind of phenomena and to keep alert to forthcoming
meteorological reports.
</P>
<P>
It's expected that Debby will affect Cuba, even if the
hurricane doesn't cross its territory, as its radius of influence
is calculated upon 600 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Compact, quick-moving Debby became the first hurricane to make
landfall this season, hitting several small Caribbean islands on a
northwesterly route that menaced Puerto Rico and the Bahamas
archipelago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
