<HEADLINE> Angolan Government Highlights Role of Public Investment Programs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Public investment programs play
an important role in implementing Angola's macro-economic policy
for the coming years, said Angola's Planning Minister Ana Dias
Lourenco here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ana Lourenco made the remarks while addressing the fourth
technic-scientific meeting of the Foundation of Eduardo dos Santos,
which began on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, public investment programs will be
integrated into strategies to develop national economy and to
eradicate poverty.
</P>
<P>
Lourenco stressed that with this year's economic program, which
has been approved by the International Monetary Fund, better
conditions for economic and institutional reforms will be created.
</P>
<P>
This, she said, will inspire confidence in the country's
economy. 
</P>
